@startuml
' Polish layout: remove inline arrow labels, concise notes, legend bottom-right
skinparam dpi 150
skinparam nodesep 160
skinparam ranksep 90
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam noteFontSize 8
skinparam defaultFontSize 9
skinparam noteMargin 8
skinparam notePadding 6
skinparam roundcorner 6

top to bottom direction

actor "Support Agent (SIP)" as Agent
node "SIP / Asterisk" as SIP
node "Media Bridge\n(LiveKit / Janus / rtpengine)" as LiveKit
node "VAD (Voice Activity Detection)\n(optional, edge or ASR-side)" as VAD_Node
cloud "LLM / ASR / TTS\n(PCM16 @16k over TLS)" as LLM
node "Orchestrator / Bridge" as Orchestrator

database "Audit / Storage" as Store
actor "Caller / SIP-Client" as Caller

' Main vertical media/signaling flow (no inline labels at all)
Agent --> SIP
SIP --> LiveKit
LiveKit --> LiveKit
LiveKit --> VAD_Node
VAD_Node --> LLM
LLM --> LiveKit
LiveKit --> SIP
SIP --> Caller

' Optional direct raw audio path (no VAD) - dashed gray
LiveKit -[#888888,dashed]-> LLM : optional raw audio (no VAD)

' Control plane (dashed)
LLM -[#0000FF,dashed]-> Orchestrator
Orchestrator -[#0000FF,dashed]-> SIP

' Storage arrows: explicit short links from sources
LLM -[#006400,thickness=2]-> Store : transcripts (anon)
LiveKit -[#006400]-> Store : metrics
SIP -[#006400]-> Store : CDRs
Orchestrator -[#006400]-> Store : audit events

' Consolidated explanatory notes placed far from central lines
note left of SIP
  SIP: Session Initiation Protocol (signaling)
  RTP: Real-time Transport Protocol; SRTP: Secure RTP (encrypted media)
  ARI = Asterisk REST Interface; AMI = Asterisk Manager Interface
  SDP offers/answers negotiate codecs (e.g., G.711)
  NAT/traversal: expect ICE/STUN/TURN for WebRTC; SIP NAT issues require correct external IP/port mapping
  RTP port ranges must be opened (typical ephemeral range e.g. 10k-20k) and QoS considered
end note

note left of LiveKit
  Media bridge (implementations: LiveKit, Janus, rtpengine)
  Handles transcoding & resampling: G.711@8k ↔ Opus@48k
  Resampling or format conversion to PCM16@16k is required for ASR
  Resampling and codec conversion add latency (design estimate: ~10–30 ms per conversion)
  Requires jitter buffers and packet-loss mitigation for stable audio
  Handles RTP⇄WebRTC mapping and ICE/STUN/TURN; DTLS for SRTP keying
  Note: media flows are bidirectional (duplex RTP)
end note

note right of LLM
  LLM = Large Language Model; ASR = Automatic Speech Recognition; TTS = Text-to-Speech
  Model audio: PCM16, 16 kHz, 16-bit mono (preferred)
  Transport: WebSocket / HTTPS over TLS
  ASR/LLM streaming: audio chunking/streaming reduces apparent latency but adds design complexity
  Inference latency (model + streaming) often dominates E2E delay; measure per-model and tune chunk size
end note

note left of Store
  Store: transcripts (anonymized), metrics, CDRs (Call Detail Records)
  Implement retention, redaction and access controls; document DPA (Data Processing Agreement)
  Apply pseudonymization and limit retention to the minimum required by policy/law
end note

' Legend bottom (center)
note bottom
  Legend: solid=media/data; dashed blue=control/API;
  dashed gray=optional (VAD); green=storage
end note

@enduml
